{{doc/start}}
Renders a styled infobox for a research entry. Data is pulled automatically from [[Module:Data/Research]]. The infobox displays name, description, tier (computed from dependency depth), science pack costs, estimated total research time, and prerequisite research entries.

Pages using this template are auto-generated by <code>foundry_parser generate-pages</code>. Editors can add content below the infobox but should not modify the template call itself.

== Data source ==
Research data comes from [[Module:Data/Research]], which is auto-generated by running:
<pre>foundry_parser generate-lua</pre>
from the game installation at <code>F:\SteamLibrary\SteamApps\common\FOUNDRY</code>. Do not edit data modules directly.

== Usage ==
<pre>
{{Infobox Research|id=_base_research_iron_smelting}}
{{Infobox Research|id=_base_research_iron_smelting|image=Advanced Steelmaking.png}}
</pre>

== Parameters ==
{| class="wikitable"
! Parameter !! Description !! Type !! Status
|-
| <code>id</code> || Research template identifier from the game data (e.g. <code>_base_research_iron_smelting</code>). || String || Required
|-
| <code>image</code> || Image filename to display (e.g. <code>Advanced Steelmaking.png</code>). The module prepends <code>Item_</code> automatically. Research images are typically stored as <code>File:Item_NAME (Research).png</code>. || String || Optional
|}

== Notes ==
* Tier is calculated as dependency depth + 1 (matching the navbox tier display): research with no prerequisites is Tier 1.
* Total research time is computed as <code>seconds_per_science_item × minimum science pack quantity</code>, assuming a single [[Research Server (Building)|Research Server]].
* Prerequisites link to <code>NAME (Research)</code> pages.
* The infobox automatically adds <code>[[Category:Research]]</code> and <code>[[Category:Tier N research]]</code>.
{{doc/end}}
